                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ǵeǵǵyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ǵeǵǵyn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>gedigin</orth><form type="variant"><orth>gædigin</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>чабер</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>savory</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>чебрец</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>thyme</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Возможна связь с %igædi%i (<mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/> <w>kedi</w></mentioned>) ‘кошка’ (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gædy"/>), как это имеет место в названиях ряда растений в тюркском: валериана, иммортель (см. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1137</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is probably related to %igædi%i (<mentioned xml:lang="tr"><lang/> <w>kedi</w></mentioned>) ‘cat’ (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gædy"/>), as it is in some plant names in Turkic: valerian, immortelle (see <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1137</biblScope></bibl>).</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>